# Billing and paywall

PocketHost is a **hard paywall** hosting service. There is **no free hosting tier** and no freemium plan for new customers.

## Target model — Pay Per PocketBase (Jul 2026)

Per slot:

| Billing | Price |
| ------- | ----- |
| Monthly | **$9**/PocketBase (7-day trial) |
| Annual | **$59**/PocketBase |
| Lifetime | **$149**/PocketBase |

Each paid slot (`subscription_quantity`) adds:

- **250 MB** pooled DB data storage
- **10 GB** pooled file storage
- **One powered-on** PocketBase at a time

**Unlimited instance records** — create as many as you want. Only **power on** as many as your paid slots allow.

Checkout quantity = number of slots. Storage pools scale with quantity.

**No Pro, Agency, or tiered plans.** One product: Pay Per PocketBase with three billing intervals.

**Grandfathered** accounts (Legacy, Flounder, Founder, early `subscription=free` rows, etc.) keep prior entitlements until migrated. **Jul 1, 2026:** new price points for **new purchases only**. Existing accounts unchanged.

**`users.subscription === 'free'`** in mothership is a **legacy DB enum value**, not a product tier.

## Current checkout (until rollout)

Dashboard `/pricing` and Lemon Squeezy checkout still use **legacy** prices ($5/mo monthly, $359 Flounder lifetime) until **Jul 1 pricing rollout** ships. Agents should use **target** prices in planning copy and **legacy** prices only when describing what is live today.

## Legacy `subscription=free` accounts

Some long-time users still have `subscription=free` in the database. They are grandfathered and keep prior entitlements. **Migration/cleanup is a separate backlog item.**

## Copy rules for agents

**Do not write:**

- "free tier", "Free plan", "Hacker tier", Pro/Agency tiers, or tier comparison tables with $19.99/$49.99
- "paid plans" vs "free tier" for standard features
- "Pro subscribers" (use **subscribers** or **Pay Per PocketBase**)
- Target prices ($9 / $59 / $149) as if already live in checkout unless the task is rollout work

**Do write (target model):**

- **Pay Per PocketBase**, **$9/mo**, **$59/yr**, **$149 lifetime** per slot, **powered-on limit**, **pooled storage**
- "subscribe", "your account", "add another PocketBase"
- "grandfathered" for pre-paywall or legacy rows
- Third-party free tiers OK (Web Awesome, npm, etc.)

## Code

- `SubscriptionType.Premium` / `'premium'` = active Pay Per PocketBase subscriber (monthly or annual; DB enum name is historical).
- `subscription_interval`: `month`, `year`, or `life` (lifetime / legacy Flounder).
- `subscription_quantity` = paid slot count (powered-on cap + storage pool multiplier).
- Limits per slot: `common/subscriptionLimits.ts` (`DB_STORAGE_MB_PER_INSTANCE`, `FILE_STORAGE_GB_PER_INSTANCE`).
- Feature gates: prefer active hosting entitlement, not bare `subscription !== 'free'`, unless blocking lapsed accounts only.

Read [MEMORY.md](MEMORY.md) Billing section when touching pricing, limits, dashboard paywalls, or Lemon Squeezy flows.
